<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,475,1733]" pageId="4" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,440,1636,1663]" pageId="4" pageNumber="70">Taxonomic remarks:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. W. Lin, Luu &amp; T. C. Hsu. A. Habit and Habitat" authorityYear="2022" box="[468,740,1637,1663]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Nephoanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nubigenus">
<emphasis box="[468,740,1637,1663]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="70">Nephoanthus nubigenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares similar floral structure with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. W. Lin &amp; T. C. Hsu. A, B. Habit" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="C. W. Lin &amp; T. C. Hsu. A, B. Habit" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[1154,1303,1637,1662]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Nephoanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="prostratus">
<emphasis box="[1154,1303,1637,1662]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="70">N. prostratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the two species are vegetatively quite distinct. A detailed morphological comparison between the two species is presented in 
<tableCitation box="[136,226,1707,1733]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="9.[136,224,664,688]" captionText="TABLE 2. Morphological comparison of Nephoanthus nubigenus and N. prostratus." pageId="4" pageNumber="70">Table 2.</tableCitation>
</paragraph>
